26 year old Silvia has it all, but is still discontent, and daydreams about BDSM sex. When her husband is away on a business trip, she goes to a castle outside Rome to work as a secretary. Here she is turned into a slave.

A title referenced far more often than actually seen, this wonderful slice of late 1960's Italian decadence is best known to soundtrack buffs under its original title, Scacco alla regina. The shimmering score by the great Piero Piccioni has become something of a lounge legend.

It is worth noting that this film was shot in Techniscope, an anamorphic process that often resulted in increased grain and sometimes problematic detail issues; you'll notice the quality here is a bit grittier than what would be seen in a standard flat film of the period.


